{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:proverbs.17",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 17,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 17 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:1",
      "text": "Better is a morsel with pleasure in peace, than a house full of many good things and unjust sacrifices, with strife.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:2",
      "text": "A wise servant shall have rule over foolish masters, and shall divide portions among brethren.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:3",
      "text": "As silver and gold are tried in a furnace, so are choice hearts with the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:4",
      "text": "A bad man hearkens to the tongue of transgressors: but a righteous man attends not to false lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:5",
      "text": "He that laughs at the poor provokes him that made him; and he that rejoices at the destruction of another shall not be held guiltless: but he that has compassion shall find mercy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:6",
      "text": "Children's children are the crown of old men; and their fathers are the glory of children. 6a The faithful has the whole world full of wealth; but the faithless not even a farthing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:7",
      "text": "Faithful lips will not suit a fool; nor lying lips a just man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:8",
      "text": "Instruction is to them that use it a gracious reward: and whithersoever it may turn, it shall prosper.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:9",
      "text": "He that conceals injuries seeks love; but he that hates to hide them separates friends and kindred.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:10",
      "text": "A threat breaks down the heart of a wise man; but a fool, though scourged, understands not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:11",
      "text": "Every bad man stirs up strifes: but the Lord will send out against him an unmerciful messenger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:12",
      "text": "Care may befall a man of understanding; but fools will meditate evils.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:13",
      "text": "Whoso rewards evil for good, evil shall not be removed from his house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:14",
      "text": "Rightful rule gives power to words; but sedition and strife precede poverty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:15",
      "text": "He that pronounces the unjust just, and the just unjust, is unclean and abominable with God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:16",
      "text": "Why has the fool wealth? for a senseless man will not be able to purchase wisdom. 16a He that exalts his own house seeks ruin; and he that turns aside from instruction shall fall into mischiefs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:17",
      "text": "Have thou a friend for every time, and let brethren be useful in distress; for on this account are they born.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:18",
      "text": "A foolish man applauds and rejoices over himself, as he also that becomes surety would make himself responsible for his own friends.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:19",
      "text": "A lover of sin rejoices in strifes;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:20",
      "text": "and the hard-hearted man comes not in for good. A man of a changeful tongue will fall into mischiefs;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:21",
      "text": "and the heart of a fool is grief to its possessor. A father rejoices not over an uninstructed son; but a wise son gladdens his mother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:22",
      "text": "A glad heart promotes health; but the bones of a sorrowful man dry up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:23",
      "text": "The ways of a man who unjustly receives gifts in his bosom do not prosper; and an ungodly man perverts the ways of righteousness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:24",
      "text": "The countenance of a wise man is sensible; but the eyes of a fool go to the ends of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:25",
      "text": "A foolish son is a cause of anger to his father, and grief to her that bore him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:26",
      "text": "It is not right to punish a righteous man, nor is it holy to plot against righteous princes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:27",
      "text": "He that forbears to utter a hard word is discreet, and a patient man is wise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.17.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 17:28",
      "text": "Wisdom shall be imputed to a fool who asks after wisdom: and he who holds his peace shall seem to be sensible.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
